# TinyURL SaaS - Project Context (Source of Truth)

## Business Summary
URL Shortener & Link Manager SaaS targeting the $1.1B market.
Positioning: Full-featured at $15/mo - cheaper than Bitly Growth ($29), with features no competitor offers at this price.
Key differentiators: No ads ever, link expiry, retargeting pixels, UTM presets, link-in-bio, smart redirects.

## Pricing Tiers
- Starter: Free - 50 links/mo, basic analytics 30 days, static QR
- Pro: $15/mo - unlimited links, 1 custom domain, forever analytics, expiry, UTM, pixels, dynamic QR, Chrome ext, bio page, API
- Business: $49/mo - everything Pro + 5 seats, 3 domains, smart redirects, workspaces, white-label QR, Zapier

## Tech Stack
- Backend: Fastify + Prisma + PostgreSQL + Redis (Node.js 20)
- Frontend: Next.js 14 (App Router) + Redux Toolkit + Tailwind CSS
- Admin: Next.js 14 (separate package)
- Extensions: React + Vite (Chrome, Etsy, Canva), Shopify Remix app
- Payments: Razorpay (30-day free trial on Pro/Business)
- Auth: JWT (access 15min + refresh 7d) + Google OAuth
- Email: Nodemailer + Gmail SMTP (GMAIL_USER, GMAIL_APP_PASSWORD)
- Infra: Docker + docker compose (postgres, redis, backend)

## STRICT BACKEND ARCHITECTURE (NEVER DEVIATE)
```
src/
  routes/      → ONLY register route paths + attach controller methods
  controllers/ → ONLY validate input (zod), try/catch, call service, return response
  services/    → ONLY business logic (plan checks, rules, orchestration)
  repos/       → ONLY Prisma calls (no business logic)
  lib/         → prisma.ts, redis.ts, auth.ts, mailer.ts
  plugins/     → fastify plugins
```

### Route file example:
```ts
// routes/auth.ts
export async function authRoutes(app: FastifyInstance) {
  app.post('/register', authController.register)
  app.post('/login', authController.login)
}
```

### Controller file example:
```ts
// controllers/auth.controller.ts
export const register = async (req, reply) => {
  try {
    const data = registerSchema.parse(req.body)  // validate
    const result = await authService.register(data)
    return reply.code(201).send(result)
  } catch (err) {
    return handleError(reply, err)
  }
}
```

### Service file example:
```ts
// services/auth.service.ts
export const register = async (data) => {
  // business logic: check exists, hash password, create trial
  const exists = await userRepo.findByEmail(data.email)
  if (exists) throw new AppError('Email taken', 409)
  ...
}
```

### Repo file example:
```ts
// repos/user.repo.ts
export const findByEmail = (email: string) =>
  prisma.user.findUnique({ where: { email } })
```

## STRICT FRONTEND ARCHITECTURE (NEVER DEVIATE)
```
app/
  (page)/
    page.tsx      → UI ONLY (JSX, no logic)
    utils.ts      → page-specific logic, formatters, helpers
store/
  slices/         → Redux slices (state + reducers)
  api/            → RTK Query API slices (all API calls)
components/       → shared UI components
hooks/            → custom hooks
```

### Frontend rules:
- page.tsx: ONLY JSX, imports from utils.ts and store
- utils.ts: formatters, validators, derived data logic
- ALL API calls via RTK Query (store/api/)
- ALL state via Redux Toolkit (store/slices/)
- NO useState for server data - use RTK Query
- useState only for local UI state (modal open, form input)

## Monorepo Structure
```
/
├── apps/
│   ├── backend/          # Fastify API (routes/controller/service/repo)
│   ├── frontend/         # Next.js user app
│   ├── admin/            # Next.js admin panel
│   ├── chrome-ext/       # Chrome extension (React+Vite)
│   ├── shopify-ext/      # Shopify app (Remix)
│   ├── etsy-ext/         # Etsy browser extension (React+Vite)
│   └── canva-ext/        # Canva app (React+Vite)
├── packages/
│   └── shared/           # Shared types, utils, constants
├── docker-compose.yml
├── .env.example
└── package.json
```

## Backend API Routes
- POST /auth/register, /auth/login, /auth/google, /auth/refresh, /auth/logout, GET /auth/me
- POST /auth/verify-email, POST /auth/resend-verification, POST /auth/forgot-password, POST /auth/reset-password
- GET/POST/PATCH/DELETE /links, GET /:slug (redirect)
- GET /analytics/:linkId, GET /analytics/:linkId/clicks, GET /analytics/overview
- POST /subscriptions/create-order, POST /subscriptions/verify, POST /subscriptions/webhook, GET /subscriptions/plans, POST /subscriptions/cancel
- POST /qr/:linkId, GET /qr/:linkId
- GET/POST/DELETE /utm-templates
- GET/POST/DELETE /pixels
- GET/POST/PATCH/DELETE /workspaces, POST/DELETE /workspaces/:id/members
- GET/POST/DELETE /api-keys
- GET/PATCH /bio, GET /bio/:slug (public)
- GET /admin/users, GET /admin/stats, PATCH /admin/users/:id

## Database Models (Prisma)
User, Link, Click, UTMTemplate, Workspace, WorkspaceMember, Subscription, ApiKey, BioPage, Pixel

## Redis Usage
- link:{slug} → JSON (TTL 1hr) - redirect cache
- rl:{ip} → rate limit counter
- bl:{jti} → logout blacklist (TTL 15min)

## Email (Nodemailer + Gmail)
- GMAIL_USER=your@gmail.com
- GMAIL_APP_PASSWORD=xxxx xxxx xxxx xxxx (16-char app password)
- Templates: welcome, email-verify, password-reset

## Key Business Rules
- 30-day free trial on Pro/Business - no credit card at signup
- Free plan: 50 links/mo hard limit, 30-day analytics retention
- Pixels: Pro+ only | Smart redirects: Business only | Workspaces: Business only
- API keys: Pro+ only

## SEO Strategy
- Target: "bitly alternative", "url shortener with analytics", "free link shortener", "custom url shortener", "link shortener for etsy sellers"
- 10 MDX blog posts in frontend/content/blog/
- Landing page: OG tags, JSON-LD, sitemap.xml, robots.txt

